ds/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients-730x730.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients-700x700.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients-550x550.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients-156x156.jpg 156w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients-288x288.jpg 288w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients-500x500.jpg 500w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/baked-salmon-ingredients.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"h-tips-amp-notes\"\u003eTips \u0026amp; Notes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThaw frozen salmon by leaving it in the refrigerator the night before you plan to use it. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eI love to mix soy sauce with: miso, gochujang paste or black bean paste most often for my sauce. Sometimes I will mix BBQ sauce and soy sauce for a simple Korean BBQ type sauce. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eI also sometimes brush the salmon with a hot sauce before baking like: Frank’s, Sriracha or Cholula. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eAnother option is to go heavy with a dry seasoning mix or rub like: Za’atar, \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/taco-seasoning-recipe/\"\u003etaco seasoning\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/chili-seasoning/\"\u003echili seasoning\u003c/a\u003e, or \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/italian-seasoning/\"\u003eItalian seasoning\u003c/a\u003e. I especially like this option if I am planning to add the baked salmon to a salad. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eI also think keeping it super simple and topping the salmon with a little melted butter, lemon juice and salt and pepper is great too!\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\